key_points: A body discovered in Wyoming has been identified as Gabby Petito, a 22-year-old reported missing earlier this month.
Initial manner of death has been ruled a homicide; cause of death pending final autopsy results.
Autopsy performed by Brent Blue, the Teton County Coroner, after the body was found in Grand Teton National Park.
FBI Denver completed a forensic search of the campground, asking anyone in the area from August 27-30 to contact investigators.
FBI emphasizes commitment to holding those responsible for Petito's death accountable, names Brian Laundrie as a person of interest.
Petito's family attorney thanked the press for giving the family time to grieve, indicated a forthcoming statement.
Investigators searching for Petito's fianc√©, Brian Laundrie, in Florida's Carlton Reserve; his whereabouts remain unknown.
Police responded to a domestic dispute between the couple in Moab, Utah, on August 12, classified as a 'mental health break'.
Petito's last known contact with family was in late August; she was reported missing on September 11.
Petito intended to marry Laundrie; her friend expresses profound disappointment and calls Laundrie a 'coward'.
spokespersons: Richard Benson Stafford (Attorney for Petito's family)
